{\rtf1\ansi\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0 Calibri;}{\f1 Courier New;}}\paperw11907\paperh16840\margl1440\margr1440\margt1080\margb1080\fs22 Contact Book Manager\line \line Assignment Information\line Dar es Salaam Institute of Technology\line Civil Engineering Department\line Module: Programming Fundamentals for Technicians (GST 05117)\line Class: OD24CE-2 | Assignment Type: Group | Assignment No: 3\line Group Number: 11 | Submission Date: March 1, 2026\line \line Group Members\line 1. ABDULAZIZ MAHYORO (240121429579)\line 2. LAWRENCE MMATAMBWE (220121417491)\line 3. ELIAH HANGO (240121476067)\line 4. HUSSEIN OMARY (240121449049)\line 5. ROBERT JAMES (240121479897)\line 6. GIDEON OLANG'U (240121429421)\line 7. MOSES MFUSE (24012317533)\line 8. GLORIA DAUDI (240121453512)\line \line Brief Explanation (One-Page Summary)\line This mini project was prepared by Group 11 to practice core C programming skills in a direct and practical way. The main goal is to let a user enter data, process that data logically, and get a clear output report.\line In this project (Contact Book Manager), c program to add, list, search, and delete contacts using an in-memory array.\line \line How the Program Works\line 1. It shows a clear prompt/menu to the user.\line 2. It accepts and validates user input to avoid wrong values.\line 3. It processes data using conditions, loops, and calculations.\line 4. It prints final results in a readable format.\line \line Concepts Practiced\line - Arrays and structs\line - String handling (fgets, strcmp, strstr)\line - Loops\line - Functions\line - Input validation\line - Menu systems\line \line Sample Output (short example)\line === Contact Book Manager ===\line 1. Add Contact\line 2. List Contacts\line 3. Search Contact\line 4. Delete Contact\line 5. Exit\line Choose an option: 2\line No.  Name                 Phone              Email\line \line Presentation Note\line This mini project is intentionally simple, focused, and easy to explain during presentation.}